commitResults.messageTitle: Rename Duke to Kee. Add Greet and Exit methods.

commitResults.messageBody:
Add echo and startChat methods to Kee.java
echo returns the input string
startChat initializes a Scanner for user input
and checks for "bye" to exit the chat loop

Add a new ToDo class to manage tasks given by the user.
ToDo class allows adding tasks and listing all tasks.
Remove echo() and added addTask() and listTasks() methods
to Kee.java.

Create multiple classes TaskManager, Task, CommandPackage, Reader, ToDo
as well as enumeration Command
Move printing of statements to TaskManager from Kee
Add mark and unmark features to TaskManager

Create new Deadline and Event classes
Add DEADLINE and EVENT commands to Command enum
Expand CommandPackage constructors to handle new commands
Update Reader to parse new command formats
Update TaskManager to manage Deadline and Event tasks

This commit was made as I forgot to staged the
new classes in the previous commit

Add a new exception class 'KeeException' to handle
exceptions specific to the Kee application.
Changed the read method in Reader.java to throw KeeException.
Kee class now handles KeeException with try and catch blocks.

Add new command DELETE.
Users can now delete tasks using task number or name.
Add new exception handling for task deletion.

Create new classes Storage to handle file operations.
Create StorageException to handle exceptions
related to file operations.
Add toData() method to Task and its subclasses.
Add new programs in TaskManager and Kee to handle
saving and loading tasks from file.

This merge incorporates the saving feature from
branch 'branch-Level-7' into the current branch.

Modified EXPECTED.TXT and input.txt to include
text-to-ui testing for Kee.
Modified TaskManager to correct the mark method

commitResults.messageTitle: Add DateTime feature using Java LocalDateTime
commitResults.messageBody:
Deadline and Event classes now take in type DateTime
instead of String for their date and time attributes.
Users must follow the format "dd/MM/yyyy HH:mm"
to input the date and time correctly.

New DateException class is created to handle
invalid date formats. A new static method parseDate in
Reader class is added to parse the date and time
from user input and throw DateException
if the format is incorrect.

In the future, let's consider moving the printing
of statements to a separate class for better
separation of concerns.

Create new UI class to handle user interface interactions
instead of handling them separately in
Kee.java and TaskManager.java.

This merge fulfills the requirements for Level 8
as well as A-OOP portions of the project.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add new package structure for Kee application
commitResults.messageBody:
Create main package Kee with subpackages
Kee.Command, Kee.Exception, Kee.Task.
Separate the classes into their respective packages
for better organization and maintainability.
Update text-ui-test files to reflect the new
package structure.
In the future, let's ensure that we maintain
a consistent package structure for clarity.

commitResults.messageTitle: Integrate project with Gradle build system
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously the project was not set up with Gradle,
making it difficult for build processes.

This commit modifies build.gradle to include necessary
configurations for the project.

In the future, let's employ Gradle for all
build tasks.
